Bury the potato into the pot of cutting compost, allowing the stem to emerges. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5a/Breed-Purple-Roses-Step-13Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Breed-Purple-Roses-Step-13Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/5/5a/Breed-Purple-Roses-Step-13Bullet2.jpg/aid4893759-v4-728px-Breed-Purple-Roses-Step-13Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
